{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.10 QA-side command-9 composition re-entered a live sealed-runtime inventory verifier and escaped before report publication in the intentionally larger QA environment."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Binding creation substituted its smaller caller interpreter for the preformal report's recorded QA interpreter, so a genuinely unequal QA/runtime pair would fail before binding publication."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Command 10 initially retained hashes without the complete package/root/standard-library/ownership inventory and fresh-child identity objects required for independent recomputation."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Recorded QA verification and strict live runtime verification were not cleanly separated, allowing ambient QA dependency identity to contaminate closure, binding, coverage, Python, and platform checks."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The standard-library launcher shape-checked command 9 without requiring its full receipt or cross-linking closure, producer, result, attempt, and completion digests to independently reopened evidence."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The standard-library launcher did not bind command 10's conformance and restart identities to the formal binding's audit-execution object."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"An ordinary semantic-validation exception could escape the preformal generator instead of producing an exact failed check and truthful nonzero generation envelope."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Adversarial coverage needed explicit unequal QA/runtime sets, forbidden ambient inventory APIs, full command-9 and command-10 mutations, rebound nonempty stderr, canonical JSON ambiguity, and retained prior-evidence inode/byte invariance."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"Active CLI/refusal text and the Makefile runtime type-check target retained stale v1.10 or partial-gate descriptions after migration."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Commands 1 through 8 are authorized through the accepted binding and terminal-bound independent preflight; the standard-library launcher's additional direct report semantics are deliberately limited to runtime commands 9 and 10."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The sealed scientific block, four scientific kernel sources, model, optimizer, planner, budgets, metrics, thresholds, and exclusions remain unchanged while v1.11 uses fresh masters and namespaces."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"One reviewed wheel was installed non-editably into separate fresh QA and runtime environments; their Prospect distribution digests match, the 45-row runtime lock verifies, QA-only tools are absent from runtime, and CUDA is available on the RTX 3050."},{"id":"F013","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The custody model trusts the same principal, kernel, filesystem, base interpreter, and cooperating writers and provides neither hostile-writer resistance nor external attestation."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"34cca0272e0ff7f1b250a3d5f506c68bb277962dceb17d87069c200c21b27144"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistem